{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δῐκαι-όω</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> ἐδικαίευν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.100: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> -ώσω Oracle texts cited in [same work][<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5.92.β, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.26\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>-ώσομαι</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. author] 3.40 \">Refs</a>]:<i>aorist</i> ἐδικαίωσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.71 \">Refs</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> <b>-ωθήσομαι</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Sir.18.2 \">LXX</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐδικαιώθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 393 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> δεδικαίωμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Eze.21.13(18). \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>set right,</b> νόμος.. δικαιῶν τὸ βιαιότατον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 169.3; δικαιωθείς \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>proved, tested,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus [prev. cited] \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>hold</b> or <b>deem right, claim</b> or <b>demand as a right,</b> with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.89, 133, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 31; δεινά με δικαιοῖ δρᾶν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 640, compare 575; δικαιοῦντες μὴ ἀφαιρεθῆναι αὐτήν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.41: with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i> omitted, οὕτω δ. (i.e. γενέσθαι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.42 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δίκας δ. (i.e. γενέσθαι)[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 93; ὅποι ποτὲ θεὸς δικαιοῖ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 781; οὐ